# order_processing.meridian
# Rules and workflows for processing customer orders.

# Rules

A customer with status suspended must not place orders.

A customer must not place an order whose total amount is more than their credit limit.

An order with total amount more than the high value threshold must be approved by an account manager before fulfillment.

When an order has been on hold for more than 7 days, escalate the order to the account manager of the customer who placed the order.

# Workflows

To process an order placed by a customer:
  validate the order.
  check the credit of the customer for the order's total amount.
  screen the order for fraud for the customer.
  obtain account manager approval for the order for the customer.
  finalize payment for the order placed by the customer.

To leniently sync analytics for an order placed by a customer:
  record analytics for the order placed by the customer.
